      • execute

        public Action execute(BiConsumer<EObject,Action> registry,
                      ProgressMonitor progressMonitor)
               throws Exception
        Calls createAction() to creates an action and contained actions, configures it to the extent possible with the action hierarchy being built and not all action being available. Configuration which requires action cross-referencing shall be performed in resolve() and be invoked by a EObjectActionResolver adapter execute() method. The adapter is created and attached in this method. Resolve adapter is composite and execute() shall be invoked only for the root action's adapter if it is present. The resolving adapter removes itself upon resolution.
        Specified by:
        execute in interface Function<BiConsumer<EObject,Action>,Action>
        Throws:
        Exception

      • newAction

        protected Action newAction(BiConsumer<EObject,Action> registry,
                           Consumer<Consumer<EObjectActionResolver.Context>> resolveConsumer,
                           ProgressMonitor progressMonitor)
                    throws Exception
        Called by createAction(). If target is and instance of ModelElement and its actionPrototype reference is set then, if the prototype is Action, its copy is created and returned. Otherwise the prototype is adapted to ActionProvider and the provider is used to create a new Action and return. If the target is not and instance of ModelElement or actionPrototype is not set, then this implementation calls AppFactory createAction(). Override to customize action creation before it gets populated by createAction().
